	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_august_04B_1867">
	
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00328</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>
	
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-08-04"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                </date>
	                <salute>
	                </salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if
	                unnecessary -->
	            </opener><!-- First page of this letter appears to be missing, below starts from uncertain page no-->
	
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">that kept my brain at work all day.</s>
	                <s id="s2">I fancied this <hi rend="underline">ought</hi> to make the walk pleasanter - but I find
	                    it destroyed it, as a rest, and so I was continually getting worse in reality, whatever
	                    temporary strength might come of the exercise.</s>
	                <s id="s3">but now, I won't so much as look at <rs key="8821113" type="person">Downes's</rs><rs key="Q80005" type="flora">ferns</rs>, which he's forever hunting up - and though I carry my hammer, and sometimes break a stone or
	                    two - I just pick up anything that looks interesting and give it to <rs key="f_crawley" type="person">Crawley</rs> to pack, without ever <hi rend="underline">thinking</hi> about it any more.</s>
	                <s id="s4">And the idler I am, the more I <add hand="#JR" place="above">find I</add> can enjoy; and
	                    one isn't always miserable because one hasn't done enough, or can't find out what one wants.</s>
	            </p>
	            <pb n="2"/>
	            <p id="p2">
	                <s id="s5">If it is fine tomorrow, I leave very early, and from <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs> will
	                    have no letter, but if it is not a good day - I'll be good instead and write <hi
	                            rend="underline">her</hi> one, too.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">mother</rs> your most <expan>affect<ex
							cert="high">ionate</ex>e</expan> son
	                </salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary
	                 -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J Ruskin</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
